85a40c65-7408-470f-9212-4283cd78b5e1.61ffdf92-bb25-4cc4-afff-bc3c586fc6b0.description=
Invokes web service methods.  This operation should not be used directly\!  Please use the wizard to build flows that use this operation.

Inputs\:
xmlTemplate - The template of the soap request to make.
inputMap - A map used to map between template names and user-friendly names. The tamplate names are pipe-delimited xpaths of the xmltemplate location, with a numerical element for lists.
url - The url to post to. 
header_SOAPAction - The SOAPAction http header field, defined by many web services for indicating the intent of the request
wswAuthenticationType - The authentication type to use for the username and password input. http is default (Uses http authentication), other options are 'ws-security digest' and 'ws-security text' WARNING\: ws-security text transmits passwords in clear-text
WSSecuritySignRequest - true or false, should the SOAP request be signed using WS-Security.
WSSecurityEncryptRequest - true or false, should the entire SOAP request be signed using WS-Security
WSSecurityTimestampRequest - true or false, should the Timestamp attribute be added to the WS-Security header
WSSecurityKeystore - keystore to use for encrypting and signing requests.
WSSecurityKeystoreType - The type of WSSecurityKeystore.
WSSecurityKeystorePassword - The password for WSSecurityKeystore.
contentType - Value to be used in the Content-Type http header
username - The username to use for authenticating with the web service
password - The password to use for authenticating with the web service
trustAllRoots - Enables weak security over SSL. A SSH certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it. valid options are\: true/false.
useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. valid options are\: true/false.
timeout - a timeout after which the connection should be terminated, or 0 for no timeout.
proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web service.
proxyPort - A port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - A username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - A password to use when connecting to the proxy.
keystore - the path to the keystore to use for SSL Client Certificates when using http authentication
keystorePassword - the password for the keystore when using http authentication
ICONCLUDE_WSW_VERSION - This value is used internally by the operation

Any additional inputs that follow these are added by the Web Service Wizard, and they are specific to the particular web service method being called.

Responses\:
success - SOAP request completed successfully.
failure - something went wrong.

Returns\:
document - raw XML response
documentStripped - raw XML response stripped of namespaces for ease in parsing with XML XPath operations

Notes\:
If you add new step-level inputs with the name header_, where  is the name of an html header, then that html header will be set to the given value in the HTTP request.
85a40c65-7408-470f-9212-4283cd78b5e1.description=
This subflow was created by the Web Services Wizard to invoke the run_command_script operation on file\:/Z\:/NA7.6_client/client/sdk/api.wsdl.gsoap. Note that the inputs to this flow which correspond to web service inputs are optional inputs.  This is due to the fact that web services definitions usually incorrectly indicate that too many inputs are required, and mirroring those settings in the flow would force you to enter unused values when running the flow.  The xmlTemplate input on the Invoke Method 2 step of this flow contains a template of the xml message to be sent, and the fields preceded by the comment "<\!--Optional\:-->" or "<\!--zero or more repetitions-->" are those which the web service indicates are optional; all others are indicated to be required.

Inputs\:
host - The host that is running the web service
port - The port on the host running the web service
DropNullElements - The input named RequestHeader|DropNullElements of the complex type\: RequestHeader
comment - The input named run_command_script|parameters|comment of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
group - The input named run_command_script|parameters|group of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
ip - The input named run_command_script|parameters|ip of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
linebyline - The input named run_command_script|parameters|linebyline of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
name - The input named run_command_script|parameters|name of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
nowait - The input named run_command_script|parameters|nowait of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
postsnapshot - The input named run_command_script|parameters|postsnapshot of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
presnapshot - The input named run_command_script|parameters|presnapshot of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
priority - The input named run_command_script|parameters|priority of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
rep - The input named run_command_script|parameters|rep of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
sessionid - The input named run_command_script|parameters|sessionid of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
start - The input named run_command_script|parameters|start of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
sync - The input named run_command_script|parameters|sync of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters
variables - The input named run_command_script|parameters|variables of the complex type\: run_command_script|parameters

Responses\:
success - The SOAP command was accepted by the web service
failure - Something went wrong while making the SOAP request

Extra Results\:
document - The raw XML response of the web service
documentStripped - The XML response of the web service stripped of namespaces
ResultSet - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/run_command_scriptResponse/Result/ResultSet
StackTrace - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/run_command_scriptResponse/Result/StackTrace/text()
Status - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/run_command_scriptResponse/Result/Status/text()
Text - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/run_command_scriptResponse/Result/Text/text()
